						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1107, Viśvāvasu, Phālguṇa 4, Bharaṇī, Sōmavāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1185 February 24, Monday</hi> on which day the 3rd <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> was current up to ·15 and Aśvinī was current up to ·53. It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king Tribhuvanamalla <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Sōmēśvaradēva (IV)</hi> and mentions his feudatory Bhōgadēva-Chōḷamaharāja as ruling from Heñjeru. It mentions <hi rend="bold">Padmaprabha-Maladhāridēva,</hi> disciple of <hi rend="bold">Vīraṇandi-Siddhānta-Chakravartidēva,</hi> and belonging to Dēsi-<hi rend="italic">gaṇa,</hi> Pustaka-<hi rend="italic">gachchha</hi> and Mūla-<hi rend="italic">saṁgha.</hi> </p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
